MORE DIRECT ATTENTION.

05:40.500 --> 05:43.300
OK, OK. I'LL SEE YOU AT
MY HOUSE AFTER SCHOOL.

05:43.300 --> 05:44.567
BEFORE I LEAVE,

05:44.567 --> 05:46.400
I'D LIKE YOU
TO SIGN A PETITION

05:46.400 --> 05:48.033
TO SAVE
MRS. ROSEMEAD'S JOB.

05:48.033 --> 05:49.934
WHO'S MRS. ROSEMEAD?

05:49.934 --> 05:52.233
OUR LIBRARIAN.

05:52.233 --> 05:54.567
THEY'RE FORCING HER
TO RETIRE.

05:54.567 --> 05:55.834
IT'S BLATANT AGEISM.

05:55.834 --> 05:59.600
MAYBE BECAUSE
SHE'S BLATANTLY OLD.

05:59.600 --> 06:02.033
LOOK, CAN WE TALK ABOUT
THIS LATER?

06:02.033 --> 06:03.100
WE'RE REAL, REAL BUSY HERE.

06:03.100 --> 06:05.867
FINE. I'LL RESPECT
YOUR SPACE.

06:08.867 --> 06:12.233
WOW. FEENY MUST REALLY
HATE YOUR GUTS.

06:14.500 --> 06:15.967
COULD BE WORSE.

06:15.967 --> 06:17.567
AT LEAST HE DIDN'T
GIVE ME MINKUS.

06:17.567 --> 06:20.000
HEY, MINKUS
DOESN'T LIKE ME,

06:20.000 --> 06:21.000
HE DOESN'T TRUST ME,

06:21.000 --> 06:22.400
AND HE DOESN'T
RESPECT ME.

06:22.400 --> 06:24.767
SO HE'S DOING THE WHOLE
ASSIGNMENT BY HIMSELF.

06:24.767 --> 06:27.900
IN MY BOOK,
STUART MINKUS IS A GOD.

06:27.900 --> 06:30.667
THEN WHY IS HE SITTING
AT THE WEIRDO TABLE?

06:35.467 --> 06:37.567
IT'S LIKE THE CAST
OF <i>THE ADDAMS FAMILY. </i>

06:40.667 --> 06:43.133
DON'T THEY CARE
WHAT THEY LOOK LIKE?

06:43.133 --> 06:45.000
WHO CARES WHAT
THEY LOOK LIKE?

06:45.000 --> 06:47.500
WHAT AM I GOING TO DO
ABOUT MY HAIR?

06:47.500 --> 06:49.600
HEY, IF YOU'RE
THAT STRESSED OUT,

06:49.600 --> 06:50.900
I'LL ASK MY SISTER

06:50.900 --> 06:52.800
WHAT SHE USES TO
STRAIGHTEN HER HAIR.

06:52.800 --> 06:55.500
YOUR SISTER
STRAIGHTENS HER HAIR?

06:55.500 --> 06:58.400
YEAH. IF SHE DIDN'T,
IT'D LOOK AS BAD AS...

06:58.400 --> 07:00.300
OH, I DON'T KNOW, YOU.

07:05.900 --> 07:08.400
MOMMY,
IF MY DOLLY IS COLD,

07:08.400 --> 07:10.900
CAN I PUT HER
IN THE TOASTER OVEN?

07:13.100 --> 07:15.200
NO, HONEY.
THAT WOULD BE A MISTAKE.

07:15.200 --> 07:16.867
MOMMY?
WHAT?

07:16.867 --> 07:18.133
I MADE A MISTAKE.

07:21.200 --> 07:23.867
CORY, DIDN'T
YOU SMELL THAT?

07:23.867 --> 07:28.500
I JUST THOUGHT WE WERE
HAVING PLASTIC FOR DINNER.

07:31.100 --> 07:33.467
I DON'T CARE WHAT
SHE LOOKS LIKE.

07:33.467 --> 07:36.300
DEBBIE'S MY DOLL,
AND I LOVE HER.

07:36.300 --> 07:38.834
WELL, SWEETHEART,
WE'LL GET YOU ANOTHER DOLL.

07:38.834 --> 07:41.200
OK.

07:42.967 --> 07:43.900
SEE YOU LATER, AMY.

07:45.400 --> 07:46.834
AMY?

07:46.834 --> 07:48.033
OR IF
YOU PREFER, MOM.

07:49.467 --> 07:51.467
I TOLD YOU.

07:51.467 --> 07:54.233
I HAVE SOME IDEAS
ON OUR PRESENTATION.

07:54.233 --> 07:56.500
SO DO I.
HERE'S WHAT WE DO.

07:56.500 --> 07:58.900
WE HIT FEENY HARD.
WE HIT HIM FAST.

07:58.900 --> 08:00.734
THE OZONE LAYER--
IT'S GOT A HOLE.

08:00.734 --> 08:03.367
WEAR A HAT.
WE'RE IN, WE'RE OUT.

08:03.367 --> 08:06.500
