BEHIND SHAMPOO

13:45.233 --> 13:47.100
IS THAT IT ACTUALLY
HAS TO TOUCH YOUR HAIR.

13:47.100 --> 13:48.300
IT'S COMPLETELY
INEFFECTIVE IF THERE'S

13:48.300 --> 13:51.100
A POLYURETHANE FORCE FIELD
SURROUNDING YOUR HEAD.

13:51.100 --> 13:53.200
I JUST HOPE YOUR HAIR
DOESN'T FALL OUT.

13:53.200 --> 13:54.700
ALAN!

13:54.700 --> 13:55.800
OH, HONEY,
A GUY AT WORK, MIKE,

13:55.800 --> 13:57.300
PUT THIS KIND OF
STUFF IN HIS HAIR.

13:57.300 --> 13:58.400
BALD AS A CUE BALL.

13:58.400 --> 14:00.467
OK.
LISTEN UP, FAMILY,

14:00.467 --> 14:02.600
BECAUSE I ADMIT I DIDN'T
KNOW WHAT I WAS DOING

14:02.600 --> 14:04.300
WHEN I PUT THIS STUFF
ON MY HEAD.

14:04.300 --> 14:07.000
AND I ADMIT I DIDN'T KNOW WHAT
IT WAS GOING TO DO TO ME.

14:07.000 --> 14:08.200
BUT HERE'S
THE THING I DO KNOW.

14:08.200 --> 14:11.400
I AM UNDER NO CIRCUMSTANCES
GOING TO SCHOOL TOMORROW.

14:11.400 --> 14:14.100
IS THAT CLEAR?
NO SCHOOL FOR CORY.

14:14.100 --> 14:16.133
SCHOOL, CORY, NO.

14:16.133 --> 14:18.567
ALL RIGHT.
NEXT UP FOR ORAL REPORTS--

14:18.567 --> 14:20.834
MISS LAWRENCE
AND MR. MATTHEWS.

14:20.834 --> 14:21.834
LET'S GO, MR. MATTHEWS.

14:21.834 --> 14:24.233
REMOVE YOUR CAP
AND DELIVER YOUR REPORT.

14:24.233 --> 14:26.467
UH, I CAN'T
REMOVE MY CAP,

14:26.467 --> 14:28.767
BECAUSE OUR REPORT
IS ON THE OZONE LAYER,

14:28.767 --> 14:34.400
AND THE CAP, UH, IS PART OF
OUR UV-PROTECTION ANGLE.

14:34.400 --> 14:36.667
NO CAPS
IN MY CLASS.

14:36.667 --> 14:40.734
MR. FEENY, IF THERE WAS
ONE SHRED OF HUMANITY IN YOU,

14:40.734 --> 14:42.400
YOU'LL LET ME KEEP THIS ON.

14:42.400 --> 14:44.400
TOO MANY YEARS
OF SIXTH GRADERS

14:44.400 --> 14:47.200
HAVE BLED ME
OF MY HUMANITY.

14:47.200 --> 14:49.500
TAKE OFF YOUR CAP.

14:53.200 --> 14:55.567
[LAUGHING]

15:02.734 --> 15:04.600
GO AHEAD, LAUGH.

15:04.600 --> 15:07.967
YOUR HAIR LOOKS DIFFERENT.
WHY WOULD I LAUGH?

15:21.000 --> 15:23.033
OVER HERE...
DUCK HEAD.

15:23.033 --> 15:26.667
[LAUGHING]

15:26.667 --> 15:27.700
Topanga: CORY...

15:27.700 --> 15:30.467
THERE'S A SEAT
FOR YOU HERE.

15:39.133 --> 15:40.300
TOFU?

15:48.600 --> 15:51.100
I ONLY GOT ONE SIGNATURE
ON OUR PETITION.

15:51.100 --> 15:52.734
IT'S SO SAD.

15:52.734 --> 15:56.100
HOW COME NO ONE CARES
ABOUT MRS. ROSEMEAD?

15:56.100 --> 15:58.200
BECAUSE SHE'S,
LIKE, OLD.

15:58.200 --> 15:59.867
IN EASTERN CULTURE,

15:59.867 --> 16:02.367
OLD PEOPLE ARE VALUED
FOR THEIR KNOWLEDGE.

16:02.367 --> 16:03.600
DARREN,
I'VE BEEN MEANING

16:03.600 --> 16:06.467
TO ASK YOU SOMETHING
SINCE THE FOURTH GRADE.

16:06.467 --> 16:08.367
EVERY DAY YOU COME
TO SCHOOL WITH A CAPE.

16:08.367 --> 16:10.734
WHAT'S THE DEAL
WITH THE CAPE?

16:10.734 --> 16:12.767
WHAT CAPE?

16:15.734 --> 16:18.600
LOOK, COULD SOMEONE ELSE
TAKE THIS FOR A WHILE?

16:18.600 --> 16:20.900
I'M GETTING TIRED OF
HAVING LIMA BEANS

16:20.900 --> 16:22.500
AND SPIT WADS
SHOT AT ME ALL DAY.

16:22.500 --> 16:24.100
I'LL TAKE IT.

16:24.100 --> 16:27.867
I'M USED TO HAVING OBJECTS
HURLED AT MY HEAD.

16:27.867 --> 16:30.000
NO ONE'S GOING TO
SIGN YOUR PETITION.

16:30.000 --> 16:31.500
WHY NOT?

16:31.500 --> 16:33.200
BECAUSE YOU'RE WEIRD.

16:35.100 --> 16:37.100
HOWEVER, I SAY THAT
RESPECTFULLY

16:37.100 --> 16:39.967
SINCE I AM
NOW ONE OF YOU.

16:39.967 --> 16:42.100
BUT I KNOW HOW
TO GET THEM TO SIGN.

16:42.100 --> 16:44.300
WHY SHOULD WE
LISTEN TO YOU?

16:44.300 --> 16:46.934
YOU DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
WHO MRS. ROSEMEAD WAS.

16:46.934 --> 16:48.600
I DON'T HAVE TO KNOW
MRS. ROSEMEAD.

16:48.600 --> 16:49.767
ALL I HAVE TO KNOW
IS THE PEOPLE

16:49.767 --> 16:51.400
WHO YOU WANT
TO SIGN THE PETITION.

16:51.400 --> 16:53.133
WE KNOW WHO THEY ARE.

16:53.133 --> 16:55.500
THEY'RE PEOPLE LIKE THAT
RIGHT OVER THERE.

16:55.500 --> 16:59.300
THEY MIGHT AS WELL BE
A BILLION MILES AWAY.

16:59.300 --> 17:01.567
YOU DON'T KNOW
A THING ABOUT THEM.

17:01.567 --> 17:03.300
WHAT DO THEY LIKE
TO DO AFTER SCHOOL?

17:03.300 --> 17:04.867
WHAT DO THEY LIKE
TO WATCH ON TV?

17:04.867 --> 17:05.867
<i>CROSSFIRE? </i>

17:05.867 --> 17:07.100
<i>MacNEIL-LEHRER </i>
<i>REPORT. </i>

17:07.100 --> 17:10.834
I ENJOY ANYTHING
WITH ANGELA LANSBURY.

17:10.834 --> 17:12.133
ALL RIGHT.

17:12.133 --> 17:15.700
I'LL ASSUME THOSE ARE
ALL ACTUAL SHOWS.

17:15.700 --> 17:17.100
THEY'RE NOT
WATCHING THOSE.

17:17.100 --> 17:19.500
THEY'RE OUT THERE WATCHING
<i>BEAVIS AND BUTTHEAD. </i>

17:23.133 --> 17:24.100
All: WHOM?

17:25.400 --> 17:27.233
EXACTLY MY POINT.

17:27.233 --> 17:29.000
YOU WANT TO SELL
YOUR IDEA,

17:29.000 --> 17:30.300
YOU NEED TO KNOW
YOUR BUYER.

17:30.300 --> 17:32.567
YOU GOT TO ORGANIZE,
YOU GOT TO STRATEGIZE.

17:32.567 --> 17:33.967
AND MOST OF ALL,

17:33.967 --> 17:38.400
YOU NEED PEOPLE
WHO AREN'T...YOU.

17:38.400 --> 17:40.667
ARE YOU PROPOSING
TO HELP US?

17:40.667 --> 17:42.200
YEAH,
I GUESS I AM.

17:42.200 --> 17:43.400
WHY?

17:43.400 --> 17:46.367
BECAUSE LIFE IS STRANGE,
AND NOW SO AM I.

18:05.467 --> 18:07.934
OK. WHAT I'M DOING IS...

18:07.934 --> 18:10.867
I'M JUST TRYING TO GET
MY HAIR BACK TO NORMAL.

18:10.867 --> 18:12.834
SURE.

18:12.834 --> 18:14.467
IF YOU SAY ANYTHING,

18:14.467 --> 18:17.100
I'LL FIND SOME WAY TO
HURT YOU WHEN I'M OLDER.

18:17.100 --> 18:19.000
NOT A WORD, MAN.

18:19.000 --> 18:20.600
I MEAN, IT'S COOL,
YOU KNOW.

18:20.600 --> 18:22.734
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

18:25.567 --> 18:27.867
HEY!

18:27.867 --> 18:28.800
I OWN YOU NOW.

18:31.100 --> 18:33.700
HOW MUCH LONGER ARE WE
GOING TO WAIT FOR HIM?

18:33.700 --> 18:35.900
JUST A COUPLE
MORE MINUTES.

18:35.900 --> 18:37.667
HE'S NOT
GOING TO SHOW.

18:37.667 --> 18:39.400
WE WERE STUPID
TO BELIEVE HIM.

18:39.400 --> 18:42.133
I FEEL CHEAP.

18:47.400 --> 18:49.867
I KNOW YOU PEOPLE ARE
WAY TOO SMART AND MATURE

18:49.867 --> 18:52.800
TO FIND SOMETHING AS
DEGRADING AS THIS FUNNY.

18:52.800 --> 18:54.800
[LAUGHING]

18:54.800 --> 18:57.900
LOOK, THE BELL'S GOING
TO RING ANY SECOND.

18:57.900 --> 19:01.100
ARE WE GOING TO HELP OUT
MRS. ROSEMEAD OR NOT?

19:01.100 --> 19:02.500
LET'S ROCK 'N' ROLL.

19:04.500 --> 19:05.767
REMEMBER,
HOLD YOUR GROUND.

19:05.767 --> 19:06.800
IT'S FRIDAY AFTERNOON,

19:06.800 --> 19:10.133
AND WE ARE THE ONLY
ROADBLOCK TO FREEDOM.

19:10.133 --> 19:11.467
THINGS COULD GET UGLY.

19:12.834 --> 19:15.500
[BELL RINGS]

19:16.967 --> 19:20.767
WHAT ARE YOU GEEKS DOING?
WE'RE GOING TO MISS THE BUS.

19:20.767 --> 19:22.600
HEY, LOOK.
IT'S DON KING.

19:22.600 --> 19:24.233
[LAUGHING]

19:24.233 --> 19:25.867
OK, LOOK.
HERE'S THE DEAL.

19:25.867 --> 19:28.834
THE SCHOOL BOARD IS FORCING
MRS. ROSEMEAD TO RETIRE.

19:28.834 --> 19:31.100
WHO CARES?
IT'S THE WEEKEND.

19:31.100 --> 19:32.367
COME ON, YOU GUYS.

19:32.367 --> 19:34.200
THE WOMAN'S BEEN HERE
FOR 40 YEARS

19:34.200 --> 19:36.600
AND THEY'RE JUST PUTTING
HER OUT TO PASTURE.

19:36.600 --> 19:38.300
JUST SIGN OUR PETITION
AND WE'LL MOVE.

19:38.300 --> 19:41.133
MOVE OR DIE.

19:42.500 --> 19:45.700
OK, YOU CAN KILL US,
BUT THINK ABOUT THIS.

19:45.700 --> 19:48.800
MRS. ROSEMEAD'S BEEN HERE
FOR, LIKE, A BILLION YEARS.

19:48.800 --> 19:50.500
SHE COULDN'T CARE LESS
WHAT WE DO.

19:50.500 --> 19:51.900
HEY, LARRY, TELL THEM

19:51.900 --> 19:53.400
HOW YOU GOT OUT OF
STUDY HALL LAST WEEK.

19:53.400 --> 19:56.800
I TOLD HER I WAS TRAINING
FOR THE OLYMPIC DECATHLON.

19:56.800 --> 19:58.867
AND SHE BELIEVED YOU,
RIGHT?

19:58.867 --> 20:00.934
SHE BOUGHT ME
A DISCUS.

20:00.934 --> 20:03.867
SEE? SHE'LL GO
FOR ANYTHING.

20:03.867 --> 20:05.233
NOW, YOU KNOW WHAT'S
GOING TO HAPPEN?

20:05.233 --> 20:07.700
THEY'RE GOING TO HIRE
SOMEONE YOUNG TO REPLACE HER.

20:07.700 --> 20:09.834
AND THIS ONE'S GOING TO
HAVE SOMETHING TO PROVE.

20:09.834 --> 20:12.834
AND, MY GOOD FRIENDS,
STUDY HALL AS WE KNOW IT

20:12.834 --> 20:14.400
IS GONNA BE OVER...FOREVER.

20:18.033 --> 20:19.867
WHERE'S
THE STUPID PETITION?

20:19.867 --> 20:20.900
CAFETERIA.

20:20.900 --> 20:22.734
I'M SIGNING.

20:25.867 --> 20:27.000
WOW.

20:27.000 --> 20:28.667
YOU DID GREAT, CORY.

20:28.667 --> 20:32.200
IT WAS KIND OF COOL
STARING DOWN AN ANGRY MOB.

20:32.200 --> 20:34.934
I NEVER KNEW
I HAD IT IN ME.

20:34.934 --> 20:37.500
SOMETIMES
THE RELUCTANT WARRIOR

20:37.500 --> 20:38.734
IS THE BRAVEST WARRIOR.

20:42.734 --> 20:44.867
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO, LIKE,
KISS ME NOW, ARE YOU?

20:46.700 --> 20:48.800
WOULD IT BE
YOUR FIRST KISS?

20:48.800 --> 20:52.000
HEY,
DON'T COME NEAR ME.

20:53.367 --> 20:54.934
BECAUSE IT WOULD
BE INTERESTING

20:54.934 --> 20:57.000
IF ALL YOUR LIFE
YOU REMEMBERED

20:57.000 --> 20:58.500
THAT YOUR FIRST KISS
HAPPENED WHEN

20:58.500 --> 21:00.500
YOU THOUGHT YOU LOOKED
WEIRD, WOULDN'T IT?

21:00.500 --> 21:02.233
NO, IT WOULDN'T
BE INTERESTING.

21:02.233 --> 21:04.000
GET AWAY.

21:04.000 --> 21:06.400
BECAUSE THEN
YOU'D KNOW.

21:06.400 --> 21:07.734
IT'S NOT WHAT
YOU LOOK LIKE

21:07.734 --> 21:09.400
ON THE OUTSIDE
THAT MATTERS.

21:09.400 --> 21:11.467
IT'S WHAT KIND
OF PERSON YOU ARE.

21:11.467 --> 21:13.767
YOU SHOULDN'T KISS SOMEBODY
YOU'RE NOT MARRIED TO.

21:15.734 --> 21:18.000
HMM. YEAH.

21:18.000 --> 21:21.000
I WOULD HAVE TO FEEL
I REALLY KNEW THE PERSON.

21:21.000 --> 21:22.400
AND THAT I LIKED HIM.

21:22.400 --> 21:23.500
GOOD.

21:25.300 --> 21:26.900
GOOD.

21:41.200 --> 21:43.300
IT WAS
MY FIRST ONE, TOO.

21:54.800 --> 21:57.100
YOU KNOW, I WANT
TO TELL YOU SOMETHING.

21:57.100 --> 22:00.200
BRILLO HEAD WOULDN'T HAVE
COME TO YOUR PARTY ANYWAY.

22:00.200 --> 22:01.467
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

22:01.467 --> 22:04.400
I'M TALKING ABOUT THE HAIR
DOES NOT MAKE THE MAN.

22:04.400 --> 22:06.867
AND I SPEAK FROM
PERSONAL EXPERIENCE.

22:06.867 --> 22:08.900
YOU SHOULDN'T TALK ABOUT
PEOPLE LIKE THAT.

22:08.900 --> 22:10.900
DON'T FLATTER
YOURSELF, CORY.

22:10.900 --> 22:12.300
WE WEREN'T EVEN
TALKING ABOUT YOU.

22:12.300 --> 22:14.233
YOU CALLED ME
BRILLO HEAD.

22:14.233 --> 22:16.500
WE WERE TALKING ABOUT
MY SISTER'S FRIEND DWAYNE.

22:16.500 --> 22:18.233
WE NEVER TALK
ABOUT YOU, CORY.

22:18.233 --> 22:19.367
WE'RE NOT THAT BORED.

22:19.367 --> 22:21.300
[LAUGHS]

22:26.133 --> 22:28.033
I SEE YOU GOT
YOUR OLD HAIR BACK.

22:28.033 --> 22:29.500
YEAH.

22:29.500 --> 22:31.500
YOU LIKE IT
BETTER THAT WAY?

22:31.500 --> 22:32.700
IT'S JUST HAIR.

22:32.700 --> 22:34.100
THERE'S STILL
A SEAT FOR YOU

22:34.100 --> 22:35.600
IF YOU WANT TO
SIT DOWN WITH US.

22:35.600 --> 22:36.967
I KIND OF
PROMISED THE GUYS

22:36.967 --> 22:38.400
I'D HAVE LUNCH
WITH THEM TODAY.

22:38.400 --> 22:40.133
YEAH,
I UNDERSTAND.

22:40.133 --> 22:43.200
WELL, THERE'S ALWAYS
A SEAT HERE FOR YOU.

22:43.200 --> 22:44.800
THANKS.

22:48.667 --> 22:51.467
HEY, TOUCH FOOTBALL
IN MY BACKYARD
AFTER SCHOOL.

22:51.467 --> 22:54.100
YEAH...
I'LL BE THERE.
